This paper discusses a reinforcement learning approach, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on policy search algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems, indicating a potential fit for the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also discusses theoretical guarantees and performance bounds, suggesting a potential fit for the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis and optimization techniques, indicating a potential fit for the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
